Case Study: UPI / Online Payment Fraud

UPI fraud is one of the most common online crimes in which an individual is duped of money or is tricked into revealing critical information 
related to their bank account. UPI fraud is said to have risen exponentially in recent times.
The modus operandi of UPI fraud is as follows: The fraudster establishes communication with the victim by phone call, SMS, or other
messaging platforms in the disguise of a bank official, customer care representative, or even an end-user of the product/service. 
The fraudster first wins the confidence of the victim by promising to return money, offering gifts, or providing timely assistance. 
Once the victim is convinced of the fraudster’s intentions, he/she is directed to send a UPI payment request or is given a link to click.
The victim is told to enter his/her UPI PIN code or click on the link in order to receive money. However, in reality, the victim is tricked 
into sending money to the fraudster.
These scams generally happen to individuals who are not aware of digital security, such as elderly citizens, students, and 
first-time digital payment users.
The effects can be serious, and they may end up losing a lot of money within a matter of minutes. 
In order to avoid these scams, one should not share their UPI PIN, should not click on unknown links, and should verify payment requests.
